What HTML Character Entities Look Like
--------------------------------------

Theyâ€™re used in HTML to represent special characters safely:

Entity       | Character  | Meaning
-------------|------------|-------------------------
&lt;         | <          | less-than sign
&gt;         | >          | greater-than sign
&amp;        | &          | ampersand
&#65;        | A          | decimal numeric entity
&#x41;       | A          | hex numeric entity

The&#32;Starry&#32;Night&#32;&#45;&#32;Van&#32;Gogh

